verbose_text: This 24-week, phase 3, multicenter, randomized, double-blind, double-dummy, active controlled, three-arm, parallel-group, non inferiority study assessed the efficacy and safety of once-daily oral febuxostat (40 mg/day or 80 mg/day) compared with allopurinol 300 mg/day in reducing SUA levels in adults from China with hyperuricemia with or without gout (trial registration number JapicCTI-132106).
